there was a little area with a sign there, that's where they used to live

moowagax --> correct! ciiresunu vs. ciires'a --> no difference, no preference (CG) ; feeling: s'a only in reparted speech or question.
nunige zeezi jaaji eera haciija hegu haciija waraire anaga higesge waza honi nigesge hegu jaagu uanaga waza uiregi zeesge hii eesge zee horohana
but, my father, wherever they were, whatever they did, they went hunting, that's what they did most of the time

zez = however that way (CG) ; isolation something distinct; seperates (CG) horohana = mostly (CG)
Nioxawani naaka haake eeja haciiwini kaga eeja ciini haciiwini
mostly we didn't live in Black River, we never lived there
niyuxani naka ke 'eeja haciiwini kaga 'eeja ciini haciiwini

before the older ones got out, they would let us go first

they would let us go first, so they couldn't catch up with us

I used to think it was enjoyable

we'd go get our own water
